    {
      "id": "0i6uA_eNY_l8j_xJ9n27s",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -7115.491177929196,
      "y": 6020.949640045274,
      "width": 420.3565372869372,
      "height": 820.5714564732148,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 70,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bu3",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1567954575,
      "version": 319,
      "versionNonce": 300228750,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1762434793864,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "- The system should automatically generate Work Entries\nfor each employee based on their assigned Working\nSchedule. These entries help determine payable working\ndays, absences, and time-off details, and are later used\nfor Payslip Generation.\n\n- Automatic Generation\n\nWork entries should be automatically generated for all\nemployees according to their defined Working Schedule\n(e.g., Monday–Friday, 10:00–19:00).\n\nWork entries are created monthly and day-wise for each\nemployee.\n\nIf an employee’s working schedule changes mid-month, the\nsystem should regenerate or adjust work entries\naccordingly.\n\n-Work Entry Status Indicators\n\nEach day in the calendar or list view should visually\nindicate the work status using colors or markers:\n\nPresent (P): Automatically marked when the day is part\nof the regular working schedule and no time off is\napplied.\n\nTime Off / Leave: If approved leave or time off is\nrecorded, that day’s work entry should reflect the leave\ntype instead of “P.”\n\nWeekly Off / Holiday: These days should appear as blank\nor blue-colored columns in the monthly view, indicating no\nwork entry generation.\n\n- Work entries serve as the payslip generation.\n\nThe system should use generated work entries to\ndetermine the total number of payable days for each\nemployee.\n\nAny unpaid leave or missing work entries should reduce\npayable days automatically during payslip computation.",
      "fontSize": 14.919481026785723,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "- The system should automatically generate Work Entries for each employee based on their assigned Working Schedule. These entries help determine payable working days, absences, and time-off details, and are later used for Payslip Generation.\n\n- Automatic Generation\n\nWork entries should be automatically generated for all employees according to their defined Working Schedule (e.g., Monday–Friday, 10:00–19:00).\n\nWork entries are created monthly and day-wise for each employee.\n\nIf an employee’s working schedule changes mid-month, the system should regenerate or adjust work entries accordingly.\n\n-Work Entry Status Indicators\n\nEach day in the calendar or list view should visually indicate the work status using colors or markers:\n\nPresent (P): Automatically marked when the day is part of the regular working schedule and no time off is applied.\n\nTime Off / Leave: If approved leave or time off is recorded, that day’s work entry should reflect the leave type instead of “P.”\n\nWeekly Off / Holiday: These days should appear as blank or blue-colored columns in the monthly view, indicating no work entry generation.\n\n- Work entries serve as the payslip generation.\n\nThe system should use generated work entries to determine the total number of payable days for each employee.\n\nAny unpaid leave or missing work entries should reduce payable days automatically during payslip computation.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
