      "updated": 1762431236193,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "In the Payroll Configuration, there are two types of salary structures: one for salaried\nemployees (Salary Structure – Reguler Pays and another Worker Pays)",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "In the Payroll Configuration, there are two types of salary structures: one for salaried employees (Salary Structure – Reguler Pays and another Worker Pays)",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "ug0RzsUOkiN5PRUpHVZ0o",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -421.7758598548992,
      "y": 11412.54418639144,
      "width": 939.46240234375,
      "height": 150,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bw9",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1355410302,
      "version": 162,
      "versionNonce": 1890521828,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1762431236193,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Each Salary Structure contains multiple Salary Rules\n\nEach rule is defined with a Category (e.g., Basic, Allowance, Deduction) and a unique Code for\nidentification.\nthe rules include conditions and computation formulas to calculate the respective amounts\nautomatically during payslip generation",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Each Salary Structure contains multiple Salary Rules\n\nEach rule is defined with a Category (e.g., Basic, Allowance, Deduction) and a unique Code for identification.\nthe rules include conditions and computation formulas to calculate the respective amounts automatically during payslip generation",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "3FKr7-JNQJga3h-i4g1_c",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 697.9597053306477,
      "y": 11463.680521259943,
      "width": 779.5792846679688,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bwA",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 213465698,
      "version": 100,
      "versionNonce": 61537628,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1762431236193,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "When you open a salary rule, you can define conditions and link the rule to the\ncorresponding Salary Component field available in the employee’s payroll settings",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "When you open a salary rule, you can define conditions and link the rule to the corresponding Salary Component field available in the employee’s payroll settings",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
